Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt:
Preliminary hearing on November 21, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
NOH sent to Def at Barron Co Jail

10:35 AM Defendant Jameck T Tolefree appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Dustin Matthew Rockow in court for Jameck T Tolefree.  Prosecuting attorney Brady James Seidlitz in court for the State of Wisconsin. 

Court relates this is a Judge Bitney case. Attorney Rockow relates time limits are waived and preliminary examination is requested.  Preliminary examination set for 10/19/2022 at 1:30 PM. 

State relates regarding incorrect mailing address.  Clerk to update DE's address to Barron County Jail.  DE to notify Clerk of Court within 48 hours of new address.  Bond continues.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant shall be fingerprinted at the Barron County Sheriff's Dept., if not already done.
If represented by the Public Defender and does not have a phone, must contact the Public Defender weekly at 715-908-8473. 

Must have no contact with C.M.D., DOB 12-13-2004.

1:10 PM Defendant Jameck T Tolefree appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Adrian W Longacre appeared by video for Jameck T Tolefree, for today.  Prosecuting attorney Brian H. Wright Aty in court for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant must call the public defender's office to determine eligibility.  If the defendant does not qualify for public defender representation, the defendant must complete a Petition for Appointment of an Attorney, Affidavit of Indigency also known as the blue form in order for the court to consider appointing an attorney.

Court grants $2500.00 signature bond. 

Next hearing to be in front of Judge Boyle, in person.
